data.name: Creamy Avocado Dip
data.quickTastyDescription: A smooth and creamy avocado dip with a hint of tanginess, perfect for dipping or spreading!
detailedCookingInstructions: Cut the avocados in half, remove the pit, and scoop the flesh into a mixing bowl.
Add lime juice and Greek yogurt to the bowl with the avocado.
Sprinkle in garlic powder, salt, and black pepper.
Using a fork or a potato masher, mash the ingredients together until smooth and creamy.
Taste and adjust seasoning if needed.
Transfer to a serving bowl and garnish with chopped cilantro or jalapeño if desired.
data.detailedName: Creamy Avocado Dip with Greek Yogurt
data.modifiersForBase: Added Greek yogurt for creaminess and tang
